name: Bench Press
description: Bench presses can be used to increase strength, improve endurance, and tone the muscles of the upper body, including the chest, arms, and shoulders.

name: Pull Ups
description: pull-ups strengthen and sculpt your shoulders, forearms, and chest (pecs). They also engage your abs, including your deep transverse abdominis, making them a great exercise for targeting many of the major muscles in the body.

name: Ab Crunch
description: Crunches have been the mainstay of ab workouts for decades. They target the rectus abdominis, the six-pack muscle that runs along the front of the torso.

name: Chest Press
description: The chest press is one of the best chest exercises for building upper body strength. The chest press targets your pectorals, deltoids, and triceps, building muscle tissue and strength.

name: Walking Lunge
description: Walking lunges strengthen the leg muscles as well as the core, hips, and glutes. You can also make walking lunges more challenging by adding weights or doing a walking lunge with a torso twist.

name: Dumbbell Lift
description: Dumbbell exercises  offer more variety than almost any other piece of gym kit going, dumbbell exercises will  help you expedite fat loss, develop total-body strength, build maximum muscle mass and even level up your cardio.
